Subject: Teaching Hackers to Hack: "The Shellcode Lab"
 training at "Hack In The Box"

Ty Miller, CTO of Pure Hacking, will be running his internationally
renowned *"The Shellcode Lab"* training course, which was run with great
success at Black Hat USA in 2011 and 2012. This is the first time that The
Shellcode Lab will be available to *Hack in the Box* participants.

Student feedback included* "By far the best course i've taken at Black Hat"*and
*"This is the BEST class I have attended in my 17 year professional career".
*

*Course Overview:*
- Create shellcode for Windows, Linux and Mac OS X (64-bit)
- Develop shellcode to do command execution, dynamic Windows payloads, port
bind, connect back, and egg hunter
- Learn staged loading shellcode, protocol tunnelling shellcode, and kernel
level shellcode
- Integrate your shellcode into publicly available exploits and create your
own Metasploit payload module
- Exploit direct and client-side vulnerabilities using the shellcode you
have developed

*Register now at:*

